INSERT INTO `wp_posts` (`ID`,`post_author`,`post_date`,`post_date_gmt`,`post_content`,`post_title`,`post_excerpt`,`post_status`,`comment_status`,`ping_status`,`post_password`,`post_name`,`to_ping`,`pinged`,`post_modified`,`post_modified_gmt`,`post_content_filtered`,`post_parent`,`guid`,`menu_order`,`post_type`,`post_mime_type`,`comment_count`) VALUES ('187','3','2013-06-04 20:44:20','2013-06-04 20:44:20','<h3><a href=\"http://www/myuhcvision.com/members/index.jsp\">UHC Vision</a></h3><p>Vision Insurance Product Overview</p><p>Â </p><p>UnitedHealthcare Vision has been trusted for more than 40 years to deliver affordable, innovative vision care solutions to the nationâs leading employers through experienced customer-focused people accessible through our diverse, nationwide vision care network.Â  Our vision plans give customers flexibility to determine their preferred funding type.Â  Our plans include covered-in-full benefits for eye exams, eyeglasses and contact lenses, as well as cosmetic coverage options.Â </p><p>Â </p><p>Our unique brand of vision care benefits administration is provided to nearly 18 million members, representing over 19,000 employer groups.Â  Clients include many Fortune 500 companies, national and regional employers, multi-employer trust funds, HMOs, insurance companies, third party administrators, associations, unions and federal, state and local governments.Â </p><p>Â </p><p>UnitedHealthcare Visionâs national network has over 30,000 providers, consisting of both private practice and retail chain providers.Â  Our network is diverse and well-balanced, offering members greater choice and convenience by providing access to evening, weekend and even walk-in appointments.</p><p>Â </p><p>We are the vision brand of one of the largest healthcare carriers in the country.Â  Our parent-company, UnitedHealth Group, drives our ability to deliver exemplary customer care and member satisfaction in the vision market.Â  The UnitedHealthcare Vision model has the professional expertise and technical resources to manage every aspect of our clientsâ vision care programâfrom start-up, communications, enrollment and customer service to ongoing administration through a single point of contact, your regionally based account manager.Â </p><p>Â </p><p><b>Network and Out-of-Network Benefits</b></p><p>Â </p><p>UnitedHealthcareâs vision care program provides innovative benefits to members:</p><ul><li><b>Eye Examination â</b> A complete eye examination is provided to members with a copay, if copay is applicable.</li><li><b>Frame Benefit â</b> UnitedHealthcare Visionâs frame benefit applies to virtually all of the frames on the market today, and most of those are covered-in-full, with no additional cost to the member, other than the applicable copay.</li><li><b>Spectacle Lenses â</b> A pair of clear, single vision, lined bifocal or lined trifocal lenses, with standard scratch-resistant coating is covered in full, after applicable copay.</li><li><b>Contact Lens Benefits â</b> UnitedHealthcare Vision provides a generous covered-in-full contact lens benefit.Â  The benefit covers-in-full (after applicable copay) the fitting/evaluation fees, contact lenses (including many of the most popular contacts on the market, such as disposables, depending on prescription and plan selected), and up to two follow-up visits. If a member chooses contact lenses outside of the covered-in-full selection, a generous allowance is provided toward the fitting/evaluation fees and purchase of contacts, and the material copay does not apply.</li><li><b>Patient Options â</b> Patient options, (not covered under the proposed plan) such as ultraviolet protection and progressive lenses are offered at a discount, which results in substantial member savings from the provider\'s usual and customary charges.</li><li><b>Out-of-Network Reimbursement â</b> UnitedHealthcare Vision provides reimbursement for services rendered outside of UnitedHealthcare Visionâs network, up to the planâs maximum allowance schedule.</li><li><b>Access to Discounted Laser Vision Correction Procedures â</b> Through our partnership with Laser Vision Network of America (LVNA), UnitedHealthcare Vision provides our members with access to discounted laser vision correction procedures.Â  Members may choose an NCQA-credentialed surgeon from LVNAâs nationwide network of more than 400 laser vision correction surgeons.</li></ul><p>Value-Added Services</p><p>Â </p><p><b>National Provider Network</b></p><p>Our national vision network includes both private practice and retail chain provider locations.Â Â  By offering access to a diverse network of providers with day, evening and weekend availability, we afford our members greater choice and convenience.Â  Our web site, <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><a href=\"http://www.uhcspecialtybenefits.com/\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">www.uhcspecialtybenefits.com</span></a></span> is equipped with a provider locator feature that displays a listing of the providers in the memberâs requested area.Â  All providers participating in our network must meet or exceed our established quality and licensing standards.Â  Additionally, in order to ensure adequate network access for our members, we are able to perform targeted provider recruiting.</p><p>Â </p><p><b>Materials Cost Contracting </b></p><p>Through materials cost contracting, we can significantly reduce out-of-pocket costs for our members.</p><p>Â </p><p><b>Quality Assurance</b></p><p>We are committed to quality in all aspects of vision care, from provider selection to lens manufacturing processes.Â  Our quality assurance and peer review committees ensure high levels of service.Â  Providers must meet credentialing standards for inclusion in our network.Â  We also solicit member input to ensure customer satisfaction.Â </p><p>Â </p><p><b>Mail Order Contacts</b></p><p>Members may purchase mail order contact lenses online through our partner VisionDirect at a 10% discount.Â </p><p>Â </p><p><b>Program Implementation</b></p><p>We have the professional expertise and technical resources to help manage every aspect of our clientsâ vision care benefits program â from start-up communications and enrollment to customer service, to reporting and ongoing administration.Â  Our dedicated account managers work closely with the employer group and our service team to ensure a smooth implementation.Â Â </p><p>Â <b>Member Services</b></p><p>Our plan is user-friendly and supported by various self-service options.Â  ID cards are not required, and there are no claim forms or vouchers.Â  Members can access plan information and identify network providers via our toll-free customer service number, 24/7 Interactive Voice Response (IVR) and interactive Website. In particular, members appreciate our extended customer service hours and online contact lens ordering.Â </p><p>Â <b>Please note that the Benefit Summaries in this document provide a brief description of coverage. State mandates may preclude certain benefit plan design features.Â  It is not a policy, certificate of insurance or coverage document.Â  For complete details on coverage, exclusions, limitations and the terms under which coverage may continue, please contact your sales representative.</b></p><p><i>Vision benefits are underwritten by United HealthCare Insurance Company and United HealthCare Insurance Company of New York and administered by Spectera, Inc. All product options may not be available in all states.Â  Standard exclusions and limitations apply in most cases.Â  Benefit options may vary by state or group size.</i></p><p>Â </p>','Health Care - Vision','','publish','open','open','','health-care-vision','','','2013-06-13 14:15:23','2013-06-13 14:15:23','','0','https://intra-dev.asynchrony.com/help-article/health-care-vision/','0','help-article','','0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` (`ID`,`post_author`,`post_date`,`post_date_gmt`,`post_content`,`post_title`,`post_excerpt`,`post_status`,`comment_status`,`ping_status`,`post_password`,`post_name`,`to_ping`,`pinged`,`post_modified`,`post_modified_gmt`,`post_content_filtered`,`post_parent`,`guid`,`menu_order`,`post_type`,`post_mime_type`,`comment_count`) VALUES ('188','3','2013-06-04 20:44:20','2013-06-04 20:44:20','<h3><a href=\"http://www/myuhcvision.com/members/index.jsp\">UHC Vision</a></h3><p>Your vision is important to your overall health. Chances are you or a family member needs corrective eyewear, as do nearly 80 percent of U.S. adults (Jobson, April 2005). Whether your vision is 20/20 or less than perfect, everyone should receive regular vision care.</p><p>Did you know that comprehensive eye exams can spot symptoms of many health problems, such as diabetes, hypertension, high cholesterol, glaucoma, and cataracts? We partner with network providers where members receive comprehensive vision care. Our eye care providers deliver complete vision examinations, arriving at a diagnosis and treatment plan (if needed).</p><p>Don\'t take chances with your most precious possession - the gift of sight. Use your vision plan today!</p><p>Frequently asked questions</p><p><br />Customer service department:Â <strong>1-800-638-3120</strong>. Â Available Monday through Friday, from 8:00 a.m. to 11:00 p.m., and Saturday, from 9:00 a.m. to 6:30 p.m., Eastern Standard Time.</p><h3><strong>General Questions</strong></h3><ul type=\"square\"><li><a href=\"https://www.myuhcvision.com/members/UnitedHealthcare_memberFAQ.jsp#1\">Who is the subscriber?</a></li><li><a href=\"https://www.myuhcvision.com/members/UnitedHealthcare_memberFAQ.jsp#2\">Who is the member?</a></li><li><a href=\"https://www.myuhcvision.com/members/UnitedHealthcare_memberFAQ.jsp#3\">Do I need an identification card?</a></li><li><a href=\"https://www.myuhcvision.com/members/UnitedHealthcare_memberFAQ.jsp#4\">What is my subscriber identification number?</a></li><li><a href=\"https://www.myuhcvision.com/members/UnitedHealthcare_memberFAQ.jsp#5\">How often should I have my eyes examined?</a></li><li><a href=\"https://www.myuhcvision.com/members/UnitedHealthcare_memberFAQ.jsp#6\">When should my child have his/her first eye exam?</a></li><li><a href=\"https://www.myuhcvision.com/members/UnitedHealthcare_memberFAQ.jsp#7\">What is the difference between a routine eye exam and a contact lens exam?</a></li><li><a href=\"https://www.myuhcvision.com/members/UnitedHealthcare_memberFAQ.jsp#27\">What is the difference between planned replacement contact lenses and disposable contact lenses?</a></li><li><a href=\"https://www.myuhcvision.com/members/UnitedHealthcare_memberFAQ.jsp#8\">Why should I have regular eye exams?</a></li><li><a href=\"https://www.myuhcvision.com/members/UnitedHealthcare_memberFAQ.jsp#9\">What do I do if I have other questions?</a></li></ul><h3><strong>Benefit Plan Questions</strong></h3><ul type=\"square\"><li><a href=\"https://www.myuhcvision.com/members/UnitedHealthcare_memberFAQ.jsp#10\">Am I limited in the kind of frames I can choose?</a></li><li><a href=\"https://www.myuhcvision.com/members/UnitedHealthcare_memberFAQ.jsp#11\">How do I know what is covered under my plan?</a></li><li><a href=\"https://www.myuhcvision.com/members/UnitedHealthcare_memberFAQ.jsp#12\">How do I verify my eligible benefits and plan coverage?</a></li><li><a href=\"https://www.myuhcvision.com/members/UnitedHealthcare_memberFAQ.jsp#13\">How do I identify myself as a member?</a></li><li><a href=\"https://www.myuhcvision.com/members/UnitedHealthcare_memberFAQ.jsp#14\">What is a copay?</a></li><li><a href=\"https://www.myuhcvision.com/members/UnitedHealthcare_memberFAQ.jsp#15\">How do I submit a claim?</a></li><li><a href=\"https://www.myuhcvision.com/members/UnitedHealthcare_memberFAQ.jsp#16\">Can I get contact lenses instead of glasses?</a></li><li><a href=\"https://www.myuhcvision.com/members/UnitedHealthcare_memberFAQ.jsp#17\">What out-of-pocket expenses will I incur?</a></li><li><a href=\"https://www.myuhcvision.com/members/UnitedHealthcare_memberFAQ.jsp#18\">Is laser vision correction a covered benefit?</a></li><li><a href=\"https://www.myuhcvision.com/members/UnitedHealthcare_memberFAQ.jsp#19\">How do I learn more about my benefits?</a></li></ul><h3><strong>Provider Questions</strong></h3><ul type=\"square\"><li><a href=\"https://www.myuhcvision.com/members/UnitedHealthcare_memberFAQ.jsp#20\">Do I need to notify you when I select or if I change my provider?</a></li><li><a href=\"https://www.myuhcvision.com/members/UnitedHealthcare_memberFAQ.jsp#21\">How do I obtain a list of in-network vision care providers?</a></li><li><a href=\"https://www.myuhcvision.com/members/UnitedHealthcare_memberFAQ.jsp#22\">How do I nominate a vision care provider for inclusion in your network?</a></li><li><a href=\"https://www.myuhcvision.com/members/UnitedHealthcare_memberFAQ.jsp#23\">Can I visit a vision care provider outside of the network?</a></li></ul>','Health Care - Vision','','inherit','open','open','','187-revision','','','2013-06-04 20:44:20','2013-06-04 20:44:20','','187','https://intra-dev.asynchrony.com/187-revision/','0','revision','','0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` (`ID`,`post_author`,`post_date`,`post_date_gmt`,`post_content`,`post_title`,`post_excerpt`,`post_status`,`comment_status`,`ping_status`,`post_password`,`post_name`,`to_ping`,`pinged`,`post_modified`,`post_modified_gmt`,`post_content_filtered`,`post_parent`,`guid`,`menu_order`,`post_type`,`post_mime_type`,`comment_count`) VALUES ('189','3','2013-06-04 20:40:16','2013-06-04 20:40:16','<p><a href=\"http://www.myuhc.com.\">http://www.myuhc.com.</a></p><h3>This article pertains to the In Network Care</h3><p>Â </p><h3><strong>CALENDAR YEAR DEDUCTIBLE</strong></h3><p><strong>$1000</strong> individual calendar year deductible. (HRA account through Benefit Strategies will cover $251 - $1000 of this deductible)</p><p><strong>$3000</strong> family calendar year deductible. (HRA account through Benefit Strategies will cover $751 - $3000 of this deductible)</p><p>Individual deductible applies to each person covered under the policy. The individual deductible and/or family deductible must be met before benefits are paid. Family deductible is 3 times the individual deductible. Once 3 persons covered under the policy meets their deductible the family deductible is satisfied.</p><p>The annual deductible applies to all covered medical health services (except preventive care) under the policy.</p><p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Â 3 month carryover does not apply.</span></p><h3><strong>COPAYS</strong></h3><p>Physician Office Visit Copay - <strong>$20</strong></p><p>Emergency Room Copay - <strong>$200</strong></p><p>Urgent Care Center - <strong>$50</strong></p><h3><strong>EMPLOYEE OUT OF POCKET</strong></h3><p><strong>$1000</strong> individual maximum per calendar year (includes individual calendar year deductible).Â </p><p><strong>$3000</strong> family maximum per calendar year (includes family calendar year deductible).</p><p>Â Individual out of pocket maximum applies to each person covered under the policy. The individual out of pocket and/or family out of pocket must be met before eligible claims will be paid in full. Family out of pocket maximum is 3 times the individual out of pocket maximum.</p><p>Once 3 persons covered under the policy meets their out of pocket maximum the family out of pocket maximum is satisfied and eligible claims for any family member will be paid in full.</p><h3><strong>LIFETIME MAXIMUM</strong></h3><p>Network and non-network $5 million combined maximum per covered person.</p>','Health Care Benefits Overview','','inherit','open','open','','184-revision-3','','','2013-06-04 20:40:16','2013-06-04 20:40:16','','184','https://intra-dev.asynchrony.com/184-revision-3/','0','revision','','0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` (`ID`,`post_author`,`post_date`,`post_date_gmt`,`post_content`,`post_title`,`post_excerpt`,`post_status`,`comment_status`,`ping_status`,`post_password`,`post_name`,`to_ping`,`pinged`,`post_modified`,`post_modified_gmt`,`post_content_filtered`,`post_parent`,`guid`,`menu_order`,`post_type`,`post_mime_type`,`comment_count`) VALUES ('190','3','2013-06-04 20:47:00','2013-06-04 20:47:00','<h3><a href=\"http://www.myuhcdental.com/presence/release/memberlogin.asp?action=login\">UHC Dental</a></h3><p>UHC want to make it easier for you UHC understands how important it is to have choices. Thatâs why with our Dental Options PPO plan, you can see any dentist you choose â in the network or not. You have access to our nationwide network of dentists. And when you see a dentist in our network, you save money and you wonât have to submit a claim form. Some of the advantages of using network dental providers are:</p><p>â¢ You pay lower out-of-pocket costs â¢ You have access to a broad network of dentists and specialists</p><p>â¢ We require network dentists to meet strict standards defined by the National Association of Dental Plans</p><p>â¢ You can visit any network specialist without a referral</p><p>â¢ You wonât have to file any claim forms To locate a participating network dentist:</p><p>â¢ You can view the online directory available viaÂ <a title=\"www.myuhcdental.com\" href=\"http://www.myuhcdental.com/\">www.myuhcdental.com</a></p><p>â¢ You can call Customer Care at the toll-free number listed on your dental ID card</p><p>â¢ You also can see a dentist outside of our network if you like, only at higher out-of-pocket expenses. The only time you have to submit a claim is if you visit a non-network dentist. Simply pay for the service, and then submit a completed claim form to us. We will reimburse you once youâve met your deductible.</p><p>â¢ If your current dentist is not participating in the Dental Options PPO Plan, you can nominate him/her to join the network:</p><p>o Call UnitedHealthcare Dental toll-free at 1-877-816-3596 during the hours of 8 a.m. to 11 p.m. Eastern Time, Monday through Friday o To nominate a dentist, provide your dentistâs name, dental practice name, address and telephone number to the UnitedHealthcare Dental representative, or go to myuhcdental.com and complete the Dentist Nomination form. The representative will forward this information to our network development team. A recruitment packet will be mailed to your dentist, and a network recruiter will follow up with your dentist after the packet is sent to discuss potential qualification and participation in the Dental Options PPO network.</p>','Health Care - Dental','','publish','open','open','','health-care-dental','','','2013-06-13 14:12:27','2013-06-13 14:12:27','','0','https://intra-dev.asynchrony.com/help-article/health-care-dental/','0','help-article','','0');
