INSERT INTO `wp_posts` (`ID`,`post_author`,`post_date`,`post_date_gmt`,`post_content`,`post_title`,`post_excerpt`,`post_status`,`comment_status`,`ping_status`,`post_password`,`post_name`,`to_ping`,`pinged`,`post_modified`,`post_modified_gmt`,`post_content_filtered`,`post_parent`,`guid`,`menu_order`,`post_type`,`post_mime_type`,`comment_count`) VALUES ('193','3','2013-06-05 15:24:30','2013-06-05 15:24:30','<p>Voluntary Life insurance is offered to Asynchrony employees at a discounted group rate to financially help should the unexpected occur to you or a covered dependant.Â  All premiums are processed through convenient payroll deductions at a post-tax rate.</p><h3>Home much insurance can you purchase?</h3><ul><li>Employee â You can select life insurance coverage of 1, 2, 3, 4 or 5 times your salary rounded to the nearest $1,000. The maximum for any employee is the lesser of 5 times your annual salary or $500,000.Â </li><li>Your Spouse â You may select coverage for your spouse in units of $10,000 to a maximum of $250,000. The cost of coverage will be based on your spouse\'s age.Â </li><li>Your Unmarried, Dependent Children â You may select coverage for your unmarried, dependent children in units of $5,000 to a maximum of $10,000.Â </li></ul><h3>How do I report a Claim? Â Â </h3><p>Contact CIGNA Claims Customer Intake at 1-800-36-CIGNA.</p><h3>What will be needed to report the claim?</h3><ul><li>All beneficiary designations on file, including beneficiary contact information</li><li>Enrollment cards/information</li><li>Death certificate (if applicable)</li><li>Once reported, all information listed above will need to be faxed to CIGNA Life &amp; Accident Claim Services (877-300-6770)</li><li>A Claims Specialist will be assigned to your claim.</li></ul><h3>Voluntary Accidental Death or Dismemberment</h3><p>Voluntary AD &amp; D insurance is offered to Asynchrony employees at a discounted group rate to financially help should the unexpected occur to you or a covered dependant.Â Â <br />All premiums are processed through convenient payroll deductions at a post-tax rate.</p><p><strong>Home much insurance can you purchase?</strong></p><ul><li>You â Accident coverage is available in the amounts of 1, 2, 3, 4, or 5 times your salary, subject to a maximum benefit of $500,000.Â </li><li>Your Family â Your Spouseâs benefit amount will be 40% of yours or 50% if you have no dependent children, subject to a maximum benefit of $250,000. Each of your covered childrenâs benefit amount will be 10% of yours or 15% if you have no eligible spouse, subject to a maximum benefit of $10,000.</li><li>Each family memberâs coverage is a percentage of the benefit amount you select. It will depend on who your insured family members are at the time of a covered accidental loss.</li><li>You may need to request changes to your existing coverage if, in the future, you no longer have dependents who qualify for coverage. We will refund premium if you do not notify us of this and it is determined at the time of a claim that premium has been overpaid.</li></ul><h3><br />How do I report a claim?</h3><p>Contact CIGNA Claims Customer Intake at 1-800-36-CIGNA.</p><p><strong>What will be needed to report the claim?</strong></p><ul><li>All beneficiary designations on file, including beneficiary contact information</li><li>Enrollment cards/information</li><li>Death certificate (if applicable)</li></ul><p>Once reported, all information listed above will need to be faxed to CIGNA Life &amp; Accident Claim Services (877-300-6770)<br />A Claims Specialist will be assigned to your claim.</p><h2>Voluntary Long and Short Term Disability</h2><p>â¢Â Â Â  If you suffer a covered disability while insured by this plan, youâll receive monetary benefits designed to help you maintain your normal lifestyle.<br />â¢Â Â Â  This program covers disabling injuries or sicknesses that last beyond the elimination period, whether they occur on or off the job.<br />â¢Â Â Â  To receive benefits under this plan, you must be disabled (as defined below) as a result of a covered injury or sickness, and you must be under the appropriate care of a licensed, practicing physician who is qualified to treat your disability.<br />How is a disability is defined?<br />â¢Â Â Â  Disabled means that, solely because of a covered injury or sickness, you are unable to perform the material duties of your regular occupation and you are unable to earn 80% or more of your indexed earnings from working in your regular occupation. After benefits have been payable for 24 months, you are considered disabled if solely due to your injury or sickness, you are unable to perform the material duties of any occupation for which you are (or may reasonably become) qualified by education, training or experience, and you are unable to earn 67% or more of your indexed earnings. We will require proof of earnings and continued disability.<br />â¢Â Â Â  Injury means any accidental loss or bodily harm that results directly and independently of all other causes from an accident.<br />â¢Â Â Â  Sickness means any physical or mental illness.<br />â¢Â Â Â  Appropriate Care means the determination of an accurate and medically supported diagnosis of your disability, or ongoing medical treatment and care of your disability by a physician that conforms to generally accepted medical standards, including frequency of treatment and care.<br />â¢Â Â Â  Regular Occupation means the occupation you routinely perform at the time your disability begins. In evaluating your disability, the insurance company will consider the duties of your occupation as it is normally performed in the general labor market in the national economy. It is not work tasks that are performed for a specific employer or at a specific location.<br />â¢Â Â Â  Physician means a licensed doctor practicing within the scope of his/her license and rendering care and treatment to an employee that is appropriate for the condition and locality. A physician cannot be the employee, his/her spouse, the immediate family of either the employee or spouse, or a person living in the employee\'s household.<br />What are the LTD benefits I can sign up for?<br />â¢Â Â Â  This plan pays a benefit up to 67% of your monthly covered earnings â to a maximum of $10,000 per month.Â <br />â¢Â Â Â  Before collecting benefits, you must satisfy the elimination period following your date of disability. For your plan, this period is 180 days of continuous disability or the expiration of your sick leave, whichever is greater.<br />What are the STD benefits I can sign up for?<br />â¢Â Â Â  This plan pays a benefit up to 67% of your monthly covered earnings â to a maximum of $2,308 per week.Â <br />â¢Â Â Â  Before collecting benefits, you must satisfy the elimination period following your date of disability. For your plan, this period is the later of any accumulated sick leave or 10 days of continuous disability from either accident or sickness.</p><h3><br />How do I file a claim?</h3><p>â¢Â Â Â  Notify Asynchrony Human Resources.<br />â¢Â Â Â  Contact CIGNA at 1-800-36-CIGNA<br />â¢Â Â Â  Calls can be made 7:00am -7:00pm Central Time, Monday â Friday.<br />â¢Â Â Â  Outside this timeframe callers can leave a message.</p>','CIGNA Insurance (Life, AD&D, STD, LTD)','','publish','open','open','','cigna-insurance-life-add-std-ltd','','','2013-06-13 15:00:02','2013-06-13 15:00:02','','0','https://intra-dev.asynchrony.com/help-article/life-insurance/','0','help-article','','0');
