INSERT INTO `wp_posts` (`ID`,`post_author`,`post_date`,`post_date_gmt`,`post_content`,`post_title`,`post_excerpt`,`post_status`,`comment_status`,`ping_status`,`post_password`,`post_name`,`to_ping`,`pinged`,`post_modified`,`post_modified_gmt`,`post_content_filtered`,`post_parent`,`guid`,`menu_order`,`post_type`,`post_mime_type`,`comment_count`) VALUES ('206','3','2013-06-05 19:03:51','2013-06-05 19:03:51','<p>After hours and on weekends, Asynchronyâs downtown and IL offices are protected with an alarm system. Every employee will be assigned an alarm code that can be used to turn the alarm on and off. There are multiple alarm pad locations you should familiarize yourself with in case you are the first to arrive or the last to leave, or if you are working over the weekend.Â </p><p>For security purposes, Cupples 9 management also programs the elevators to a secure mode after hours and on weekends, so you will need to use your key card to gain access to both of Asynchronyâs floors during these times.Â </p><h3>Cupples 9 Alarm Pad Locations:</h3><ul><li>6<sup>th</sup> Floor Secure Space (south entrance) â inside entrance, to the left</li><li>6<sup>th</sup> Floor Secure Space (east entrance) â inside entrance, to the right</li><li>6<sup>th</sup> Floor Open Space (north entrance) â inside the entrance door to the right </li><li>6<sup>th</sup> Floor Open Space (secure entrance into open area) â inside the entrance door to the right</li><li>6<sup>th</sup> Floor Open Space (Forest Park entrance) â to the right of the door upon exiting</li><li>Forest Park Conference Room â on either side of the room inside both entrances</li><li>7<sup>th</sup> Floor â by the stairwell door in the reception/lobby area</li><li>7<sup>th</sup> Floor â by the stairwell door in the freight elevator</li></ul><h3>Seibert Rd Alarm Pad Locations:</h3><ul><li>Main entrance</li><li>Side entrance by the coffee maker</li><li>Back of office by the kitchen</li></ul><p>Â </p><h3>The Alarm is going off.</h3><p>If you enter a work area and hear the alarm pad beeping, it means you were the first to enter the space since the alarm was set the following evening. You must enter your code and press the OFF(#1) button to keep the alarm from activating and notifying the authorities. If you are the last person to leave a work area, it is your responsibility to set the alarm. Enter your code and press the AWAY(#2) button. The alarm pad will start beeping, and you have 90 seconds to exit the area without setting off the alarm.</p><h3>Oops, I set off the alarm.</h3><p>Should you accidentally set off the alarm, please immediately call the Alarm Hotline: 314.735.7698.</p><h3>Test Your Alarm Code.</h3><p>Â Test your alarm code by entering your code and press the OFF(#1) button.Â  You will here a beep.Â  If you do not hear a beep, please submit a request ticket to admin-request@asynchrony.com.</p>','Security & Alarm Systems','','publish','open','open','','security-alarm-systems','','','2013-06-13 15:35:28','2013-06-13 15:35:28','','0','https://intra-dev.asynchrony.com/help-article/security-alarm-systems/','0','help-article','','0');
