INSERT INTO `wp_posts` (`ID`,`post_author`,`post_date`,`post_date_gmt`,`post_content`,`post_title`,`post_excerpt`,`post_status`,`comment_status`,`ping_status`,`post_password`,`post_name`,`to_ping`,`pinged`,`post_modified`,`post_modified_gmt`,`post_content_filtered`,`post_parent`,`guid`,`menu_order`,`post_type`,`post_mime_type`,`comment_count`) VALUES ('224','3','2013-06-05 18:52:52','2013-06-05 18:52:52','<p>Employees at Cupples 9 are assigned to one of two main parking areas, the Cupples Garage or the surface lot on the south side of the building. Parking is company paid, but all parking is <b><i>unreserved</i></b> in both areas. Do not park in any spaces marked <b><i>Reserved</i></b> for other tenants of the building. Those who violate this rule are subject to having their car towed by building or garage management.</p><p>If you are assigned to park in the surface lot, your building access card is programmed to also open the gate arm by holding it in close proximity to the card reader at the entrance to the lot; the arm will open automatically when you exit. You will also be issued a vehicle hang tag that must be displayed inside your vehicle at all times when you are parked in the lot.</p><p>If you park in the garage, you will be issued a separate card that opens the gate arm when you are in close proximity to the card reader. You need to have your garage parking access card in your vehicle at all times. If you forget it, you need to take a ticket to enter the garage, and youâll have to pay to exit. As is the case with your building access card, the garage access card is only to be used by eligible employees and is not to be loaned to other persons for access to the garage. If your card is lost or compromised, please report this immediately to Andi Davis (<a href=\"mailto://andi.davis@asynchrony.com\">andi.davis@asynchrony.com</a>). Unless uncontrollable circumstances resulted in loss or damage to the card, a replacement card will be issued at the employeeâs expense.</p><p><img class=\"attachment-full\" alt=\"Building-Parking Picture\" src=\"https://intra-dev.asynchrony.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/Building-Parking-Picture.jpg\" width=\"1296\" height=\"742\" /></p>','Employee Parking - Cupples 9','','inherit','open','open','','197-revision-4','','','2013-06-05 18:52:52','2013-06-05 18:52:52','','197','https://intra-dev.asynchrony.com/197-revision-4/','0','revision','','0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` (`ID`,`post_author`,`post_date`,`post_date_gmt`,`post_content`,`post_title`,`post_excerpt`,`post_status`,`comment_status`,`ping_status`,`post_password`,`post_name`,`to_ping`,`pinged`,`post_modified`,`post_modified_gmt`,`post_content_filtered`,`post_parent`,`guid`,`menu_order`,`post_type`,`post_mime_type`,`comment_count`) VALUES ('225','3','2013-06-05 19:05:59','2013-06-05 19:05:59','<h3>Building and Office Access</h3><p>All Asynchrony employees will receive a key card that provides access to our headquarters at 900 Spruce St. in the building known as Cupples 9. Card readers are located at the building entrances, in the elevators, and next to secured tenant spaces, which include some stairwell doors. To gain access, employees must hold their card in close proximity to the reader. An indicator light will change from red to green, signaling that access has been granted. If access has been denied, the indicator light will remain red. If you believe access was denied in error, please submit an admin request ticket (<a href=\"mailto:admin-request@asynchrony.com\">admin-request@asynchrony.com</a>) indicating the door/area where access was denied.</p><p>The key card allows 24/7/365 access to Cupples 9 through the tenant lobby entrance on the buildingâs west side, as well as the Spruce St. entrance. Once in the building, the card should be used inside the elevator or next to the stairwell door to gain access to the 7<sup>th</sup> floor. The 6<sup>th</sup> floor lobby is accessible without the card via the elevator or stairwell, but must be used to gain access to 6<sup>th</sup> floor work areas. All cards are programmed to allow access to the north side of the 6<sup>th</sup> floor as well as the Forest Park conference room. Only eligible employees will have cards programmed to allow access to the south side of the 6<sup>th</sup> floor.</p><h3>Working at the Seibert Rd. Office</h3><p>Employees assigned to the Illinois Seibert Rd. location will be issued a separate key card to access that office as the Cupples 9 building access cards cannot be programmed to work at other sites. Â </p><p>Key cards are only to be used by eligible employees and are not to be loaned to other persons for access to the building or any of Asynchronyâs work areas. If your badge is lost or compromised, please report this immediately to Andi Davis (andi.davis@asynchrony.com). Unless uncontrollable circumstances resulted in loss or damage to the card, a replacement card will be issued at the employeeâs expense.</p>','Building Access','','inherit','open','open','','195-revision-3','','','2013-06-05 19:05:59','2013-06-05 19:05:59','','195','https://intra-dev.asynchrony.com/195-revision-3/','0','revision','','0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` (`ID`,`post_author`,`post_date`,`post_date_gmt`,`post_content`,`post_title`,`post_excerpt`,`post_status`,`comment_status`,`ping_status`,`post_password`,`post_name`,`to_ping`,`pinged`,`post_modified`,`post_modified_gmt`,`post_content_filtered`,`post_parent`,`guid`,`menu_order`,`post_type`,`post_mime_type`,`comment_count`) VALUES ('226','3','2013-06-05 19:40:11','2013-06-05 19:40:11','<p>Our phone system includes support for multi-user conference rooms.Â  We have dedicated particular rooms to specific projects or people in order to minimize collisions.Â  Be aware that the same number can only be used for one conference call at a time, so be careful if you are using the room for multiple purposes.</p><p>To connect to any of the conference rooms you will have to enter a four digit pin number. There are two different pin numbers assigned to each conference. A user pin number and an admin pin number. Once connected to conference you may press \"*\" at anytime to hear the preferences menu. Admins have additional options from the preferences menu, including muting and kicking other callers.<br />Â </p><p>Extenstion 899 - Virtual Conference Selection Menu DID: 314-678-2299</p><p>Please enter a helpdesk ticket by visitingÂ <a title=\"https://helpdesk.asynchrony.com\" href=\"https://helpdesk.asynchrony.com/\">https://helpdesk.asynchrony.com</a>Â or emailingÂ <a href=\"mailto:helpdesk@asynchrony.com\">helpdesk@asynchrony.com</a>Â to receive a Conference Number.</p>','Conference Calling','','publish','open','open','','conference-calling','','','2013-06-05 19:40:11','2013-06-05 19:40:11','','0','https://intra-dev.asynchrony.com/help-article/conference-calling/','0','help-article','','0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` (`ID`,`post_author`,`post_date`,`post_date_gmt`,`post_content`,`post_title`,`post_excerpt`,`post_status`,`comment_status`,`ping_status`,`post_password`,`post_name`,`to_ping`,`pinged`,`post_modified`,`post_modified_gmt`,`post_content_filtered`,`post_parent`,`guid`,`menu_order`,`post_type`,`post_mime_type`,`comment_count`) VALUES ('227','3','2013-06-05 19:41:59','2013-06-05 19:41:59','<p>*1 - Record call - recordings will be delivered to your voice mailbox within 30 minutes of the end of the call. Use web voicemail to download recordings.<br />*2 - Attended Transfer<br />*3 - Blind Transfer<br />*5 - Redial (some softphones don\'t have a redial button)<br />*69 - Call last external number that called you.<br />*400 - Call Queue Agent Login<br />*411 - Company Directory<br />*500 - Call Forwarding Menu -Â <b>Deprecated use *502 through *505</b><br />*501 - DND - Phone will not ring sends callers directly to voicemail. Takes precedence over Call Forwarding.<br />*502 - Toggle Call Forwarding. Takes precedence over Call Forwarding On No Answer.<br />*503 - Toggle Call Forwarding On No Answer. Takes precedence over Call Forwarding During Business Hours<br />*504 - Toggle Call Forwarding During Business Hours<br />*505 - Change number to forward calls to<br />*980 - Voicemail - Check voicemail for another mailbox.<br />*981 - Voicemail - Password defaults to your 4 digit alarm code<br />*999 - Listen to Emergency Status Message<br />. *2XX - Dials directly into voicemailbox of user with extension 2XX.<br />**2XX - Dials cell phone associated with user at extension 2XX. This is based on the users cellphone entry on his/her ownÂ <a title=\"https://asterisk.asynchrony.com/settings/main.php\" href=\"https://asterisk.asynchrony.com/settings/main.php\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">phone settings page</a><br /><b><br /></b></p><h3>Â Additional Web Features</h3><p><a href=\"https://asterisk.asynchrony.com/\" target=\"_blank\">https://asterisk.asynchrony.com</a>Â - from here you can check you voicemail, manage black and grey lists, and modify your Call Forwarding Preferences. Login using your extension number and your voicemail password.</p><h3>External Features</h3><p>All external features listed below must be entered from the Automated Assistant Menu (Sounds like \"Thank you for calling Asynchrony Solutions, if you know your parties ext.....\")<br />For all external features you will be prompted for your mailbox number and voice mail password.</p><ul><li><b>From outside the office you can dial 314-678-2212 --or--Â </b><b>888-339-9756</b><b>Â to reach the automated assistant menu</b><br />Â </li></ul><p>*500 - Call Forwarding Menu - Enables Call Forwarding / Call Forwarding on No Answer / Call Forwarding During Business Hours<br />*501 - DND - Phone will not ring sends callers directly to voice mail. Takes precedence over Call Forwarding.<br />*502 - Toggle Call Forwarding. Takes precedence over Call Forwarding On No Answer.<br />*503 - Toggle Call Forwarding On No Answer. Takes precedence over Call Forwarding During Business Hours<br />*504 - Toggle Call Forwarding During Business Hours<br />*981 - Voice mail - Password defaults to your 4 digit alarm code<br />*999 - Listen to Emergency Status Notification</p><h3>Call Parking<strong></strong></h3><p>700 - Park Extension - To park a call press *3 (to transfer) followed by 700 The parking attendant will announce a position number where the call is parked.<br />701-750 - Park Positions - Go to a different phone and dial that parked position and you will connect to the original call.</p><h3>DIDs</h3><p>The 314-678-2XXX Prefix will be assigned to extensions which connect to People (Bob Elfanbaum, Nate McKie, etc.)<br />The 314-735-7XXX Prefix will be assigned to extensions which connect to Places (1st Floor Conference Rooms, JEOD Workgroup etc.)<br />Any phone extensions that start with 3 (ex. 347)Â cannot be direct-dialed and must be accessed externally by first dialing the main number (314-678-2200).</p>','Conference Calling Phone Features','','publish','open','open','','conference-calling-phone-features','','','2013-06-05 19:41:59','2013-06-05 19:41:59','','0','https://intra-dev.asynchrony.com/help-article/conference-calling-phone-features/','0','help-article','','0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` (`ID`,`post_author`,`post_date`,`post_date_gmt`,`post_content`,`post_title`,`post_excerpt`,`post_status`,`comment_status`,`ping_status`,`post_password`,`post_name`,`to_ping`,`pinged`,`post_modified`,`post_modified_gmt`,`post_content_filtered`,`post_parent`,`guid`,`menu_order`,`post_type`,`post_mime_type`,`comment_count`) VALUES ('228','3','2013-06-05 19:51:44','2013-06-05 19:51:44','<p><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wiki\">What the heck is a wiki?</a>Â </p><p>There are two kinds of wikis currently in use. Â <a href=\"https://mediawiki.asolutions.com/index.php/Main_Page\">MediaWikiÂ </a>is used as the official company wiki that contains Asynchrony company information as well as project-based data. Ace Wiki is provided with each Ace project, but uses a wiki syntax calledÂ <a href=\"http://textile.thresholdstate.com/\">Textile</a>.</p><h3>Wiki Reference</h3><p><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Cheatsheet\">Quick reference (web version)</a></p><h3>Textile Reference</h3><p><a href=\"https://ace-deuce.asolutions.com/wiki/textile_help\">Quick reference (for version used in Ace)</a></p>','Wiki Basics','','publish','open','open','','wiki-basics','','','2013-06-05 19:51:44','2013-06-05 19:51:44','','0','https://intra-dev.asynchrony.com/help-article/wiki-basics/','0','help-article','','0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` (`ID`,`post_author`,`post_date`,`post_date_gmt`,`post_content`,`post_title`,`post_excerpt`,`post_status`,`comment_status`,`ping_status`,`post_password`,`post_name`,`to_ping`,`pinged`,`post_modified`,`post_modified_gmt`,`post_content_filtered`,`post_parent`,`guid`,`menu_order`,`post_type`,`post_mime_type`,`comment_count`) VALUES ('229','3','2013-06-05 19:55:09','2013-06-05 19:55:09','','Schafer Helpdesk User Guide','','inherit','open','open','','schafer-helpdesk-user-guide','','','2013-06-05 19:55:09','2013-06-05 19:55:09','','230','','0','attachment','application/pdf','0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` (`ID`,`post_author`,`post_date`,`post_date_gmt`,`post_content`,`post_title`,`post_excerpt`,`post_status`,`comment_status`,`ping_status`,`post_password`,`post_name`,`to_ping`,`pinged`,`post_modified`,`post_modified_gmt`,`post_content_filtered`,`post_parent`,`guid`,`menu_order`,`post_type`,`post_mime_type`,`comment_count`) VALUES ('230','3','2013-06-05 19:55:15','2013-06-05 19:55:15','<p>If you have a problem that requires technical support, such as...</p><ul><li>Malfunctioning workstation</li><li>Need for access to a server or application</li><li>Need for additional hardware for a project</li><li>Phone system not operating properly</li><li>Forgotten or expired password</li><li>Need for software to be installed</li></ul><p>... you need technical support.Â  There are two ways of submitting a ticket to our infrastructure team to get things started:</p><ol><li><strong>Send an email toÂ <a href=\"mailto:helpdesk@asynchrony.com\">helpdesk@asynchrony.com</a></strong>Â  The email subject should be the main topic of your request, and the body should contain all the information that the technical support team would require to assist you.Â  The ticket system will then create a ticket for you based on your email, and you should get an automated reply followed by assistance with your issue.</li><li><strong>Enter a ticket atÂ <a href=\"https://helpdesk.asynchrony.com/\" target=\"_blank\">https://helpdesk.asynchrony.com</a>Â </strong>Â You can always navigate to the helpdesk website to enter a ticket; you will first need to log in using your ASYNCHRONYÂ domain username and password.Â  Once you have logged in, you will either be directed to a page where you can enter a new request through a web page form, or if you have a current open ticket, you will see a list of all tickets related to you.</li></ol><p>Once you have entered a ticket, you can check on the status of that ticket at any time by logging in to the helpdesk site as specified above.Â  You can add notes to your ticket if you have more information or want to ask questions.Â  Any time a note is added to your ticket by someone other than yourself, or any time the status of your ticket changes, you will receive email notification with full information about what happened.</p><p>If you request support that requires a purchase, there is an approval process that will take place before your request is fulfilled.Â  Please note that this may take some extra time.</p><p><strong>I</strong><strong>f you have an emergency and need help immediately, you can call the Technical Support Hotline at extension 699 on an office phone or 314-735-7699 from any other phone.</strong>Â  This will will initiate an automated calling routine that will call the cell phone of each member of the tech support staff repeatedly in an attempt to get an answer.Â  If no one can be reached, the call will finally allow the caller to leave a message that will then be paged to the support staff so that you get a response as soon as possible.</p><p>What to consider when calling the Technical Support hotline:</p><ul><li>Please only call the hotline when your need requires immediate attention.Â </li><li>Before calling the hotline, please create a helpdesk request if possible.</li><li>You will hear music and not rings while the server is attempting to connect you.Â  Do not hang up; you will eventually be able to leave a message if no one can be reached.Â  Please make sure a phone number where you can be reached is on any message you leave.</li><li>The automation is set up to try to keep you from getting voicemail for one of the technicians.Â  However, it is possible that an individual technician\'s voicemail will pick up on some occasions.Â  If this happens, go ahead and leave a message with a phone number where you can be reached, and if you do not have a response within fifteen minutes, please try the hotline number again.</li><li>The hotline is not a substitute for creating a helpdesk request.Â  If you cannot create one before calling (for example, because you need a password reset), please create one as soon as possible after speaking with a technician.</li></ul>','Technical Support','','publish','open','open','','technical-support','','','2013-06-07 18:14:32','2013-06-07 18:14:32','','0','https://intra-dev.asynchrony.com/help-article/technical-support/','0','help-article','','0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` (`ID`,`post_author`,`post_date`,`post_date_gmt`,`post_content`,`post_title`,`post_excerpt`,`post_status`,`comment_status`,`ping_status`,`post_password`,`post_name`,`to_ping`,`pinged`,`post_modified`,`post_modified_gmt`,`post_content_filtered`,`post_parent`,`guid`,`menu_order`,`post_type`,`post_mime_type`,`comment_count`) VALUES ('231','3','2013-06-05 19:56:22','2013-06-05 19:56:22','<p>In an effort to promote cross-employee and cross-project communication, give employees a chance to practice presentation and public speaking skills, and keep new ideas and concepts injected into our organization, the Lunch and Learn program was initiated.Â  This is a completely employee-organized program, and all employees are welcome and encouraged to present on any work-related topic.</p><p>AÂ <a href=\"http://lunchandlearn.asolutions.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Lunch and Learn web application</a>Â has been created to keep a record of previous presentations and schedule upcoming talks.Â  As of this writing,Â Eric NeunaberÂ has volunteered to be the point of contact for scheduling presentations and encouraging participation.Â  We also try to get printed posters in visible locations throughout the office advertising the Lunch and Learn session for the current day, to help people remember to attend.Â  You will also see an invitation in your inbox that will appear on your Zimbra calendar.</p><p>Some possible types of topics that would be good for presentation might be:</p><ul><li>Introduction of a new programming language, tool, or design pattern.</li><li>Review of a particular way of designing, developing, testing, and/or deploying software.</li><li>A new program available for employees in the company.</li><li>New development processes, both practical and theoretical.</li><li>\"Enrichment\"Â topics such as skills, foreign cultures, or life enhancement techniques.</li></ul><p>Topics that are not encouraged would be those that are controversial in a personal way, unethical, or political.</p><p>PLEASEÂ NOTEÂ that time spent preparing for or attending a Lunch and Learn session is not intended to be reported as company time unless approval is granted by executive management.</p>','Lunch and Learns','','publish','open','open','','lunch-and-learns','','','2013-06-05 19:56:22','2013-06-05 19:56:22','','0','https://intra-dev.asynchrony.com/help-article/lunch-and-learns/','0','help-article','','0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` (`ID`,`post_author`,`post_date`,`post_date_gmt`,`post_content`,`post_title`,`post_excerpt`,`post_status`,`comment_status`,`ping_status`,`post_password`,`post_name`,`to_ping`,`pinged`,`post_modified`,`post_modified_gmt`,`post_content_filtered`,`post_parent`,`guid`,`menu_order`,`post_type`,`post_mime_type`,`comment_count`) VALUES ('232','3','2013-06-05 19:57:05','2013-06-05 19:57:05','<p>At Asynchrony, we know that the most valuable asset any company can have is their people. That is why we take pride in having some of the best employees in the industry. Our people enjoy a structured, yet relaxed, work environment with excellent benefits and opportunities.</p><div align=\"center\"><hr align=\"center\" size=\"2\" width=\"100%\" /></div><p>To encourage your proactive assistance in helping Asynchrony find the right people to add to our team, <b>we will pay up to a $2,500 bonus to employees who refer a new employee</b> that we hire and who stays with Asynchrony for at least 90 days (the bonus to be paid after the 90 day time period).</p><p>We are always looking for Mid-Sr level candidates for the following positions:</p><table border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\"><tbody><tr><td valign=\"top\" width=\"319\"><ul><li>Mobile App Developer (iOS/Android)</li><li>Java Developer</li><li>QA Analyst</li></ul></td><td valign=\"top\" width=\"319\"><ul><li>.NET Developer</li><li>Ruby on Rails Developer</li><li>User Interface (UI) Designer</li></ul></td></tr></tbody></table><p align=\"center\"><i>And more â View all openings at j</i><i>obs.asynchrony.com!</i></p><p align=\"center\"><b>Process for Referring Candidates</b></p><p>For referrals to be eligible for the bonus program, they should apply online at jobs.asynchrony.com indicating they are a referral from you.Â  You should also send aÂ brief write-up describing the person\'s skills and expertise to Sandi.Â Your referral email should include:</p><ul><li>How you know the candidate</li><li>How the candidate will best fit within our organization</li><li>Anything else we should know about the referral</li></ul><p align=\"center\"><b>Do Not Recruit List (April 2013)</b></p><p>The following list includes companies we partner with and, therefore, do not want to recruit from these companies.Â  This list is always changing so a good rule of thumb is that if they are a customer or we do business with them, it is better to ask before proceeding.Â  Asynchrony will NOT pay a referral bonus for any current customers.</p><table width=\"549\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\"><tbody><tr><td valign=\"top\" width=\"319\"><ul><li>Bick/Bick Healthcare</li><li>Blue Mountain</li><li>Bridgewater</li><li>CACI</li><li>CGI/Stanley</li><li>Coventry</li><li>Emerson</li></ul></td><td valign=\"top\" width=\"319\"><ul><li>LMI</li><li>OCI</li><li>SAIC â please ask</li><li>Sealco</li><li>Tricor</li><li>Trident</li></ul></td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" width=\"319\">Â </td><td valign=\"top\" width=\"319\">Â </td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" width=\"319\">Â </td><td valign=\"top\" width=\"319\">Â </td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" width=\"319\">Â </td><td valign=\"top\" width=\"319\">Â </td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" width=\"319\">Â </td><td valign=\"top\" width=\"319\">Â </td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" width=\"319\">Â </td><td valign=\"top\" width=\"319\">Â </td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" width=\"319\">Â </td><td valign=\"top\" width=\"319\">Â </td></tr></tbody></table><p align=\"center\"><b>Â </b></p><p align=\"center\"><b>Asynchrony is an Equal Employment Opportunity Employer</b></p><p>Note:Â  Recruiters are not eligible to receive referral bonuses.Â  Supervisors and other levels of management involved in the hiring decision process are not eligible to receive referral bonuses for applicants they refer if the applicant is hired for a position reporting directly or indirectly to them.Â  If a referred applicant is hired through an agency, a referral bonus will not be paid. Not all positions qualify for a referral bonus.</p><p><b><strong></strong></b></p><p>Â </p>','Employee Referral Bonus Program','','publish','open','open','','employee-referral-bonus-program','','','2013-06-13 15:10:09','2013-06-13 15:10:09','','0','https://intra-dev.asynchrony.com/help-article/recruiting-referral-bonus/','0','help-article','','0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` (`ID`,`post_author`,`post_date`,`post_date_gmt`,`post_content`,`post_title`,`post_excerpt`,`post_status`,`comment_status`,`ping_status`,`post_password`,`post_name`,`to_ping`,`pinged`,`post_modified`,`post_modified_gmt`,`post_content_filtered`,`post_parent`,`guid`,`menu_order`,`post_type`,`post_mime_type`,`comment_count`) VALUES ('233','3','2013-06-05 19:57:59','2013-06-05 19:57:59','<p>The Asynchrony Mentor Program was established to ensure new employees are given the appropriate introduction to the available resources and environment in an informal setting.<br />The goals of the program are to:<br />1. Help new employees feel they are a part of Asynchrony\'s culture.<br />2. Introduce them to their co-workers, especially those they will not be directly working with initially.<br />3. Answer questions to give a better understanding and introduction to the available resources.<br />4. Help new employees adjust to Asynchrony\'s \"unique\" culture.</p><h3>The details of the program:</h3><p>1. The new employee will be assigned a Mentor on the first day with Asynchrony.<br />2. The new employee and mentor are encouraged to start having conversations with each other.<br />3. The mentor is allowed to take the new employee to a company paid lunch 4-8 times as needed.<br />4. Mentor should fill out and turn into accounting, within one week of the lunch taking place, an expense report<br />capturing the cost of the lunch.<br />â¢ The DETAIL receipt must accompany the expense report.<br />â¢ A Detail receipt is a receipt listing all items purchased; this is a requirement by the IRS and the DCAA.<br />â¢ Mentor will only be reimbursed up to $18 per person, per meal.<br />â¢ Absolutely NO ALCOHOL will be reimbursed.<br />5. The mentor is encouraged to introduce the new employee to other employees.<br />6. The mentor is encouraged to bring the new employee to sponsored and unsponsored activities.</p><h3>Becoming a Mentor:</h3><p>1. All employees are eligible to become a mentor.<br />2. Employees interested in being a mentor should have an updated resume on the public drive under \\Consulting<br />\\Resumes\\Asynchrony Resume.<br />3. Employees wanting to participate in being a mentor need to send answers to the following questions to the<br />HR Department.<br />â¢ What is one thing you tell your friends/family about Asynchrony?<br />â¢ What is one thing you wish you knew when you started?<br />â¢ Describe one good thing about yourself.<br />â¢ Describe one thing you would like to improve about yourself.</p>','New Employee Mentor Program','','publish','open','open','','new-employee-mentor-program','','','2013-06-05 19:57:59','2013-06-05 19:57:59','','0','https://intra-dev.asynchrony.com/help-article/new-employee-mentor-program/','0','help-article','','0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` (`ID`,`post_author`,`post_date`,`post_date_gmt`,`post_content`,`post_title`,`post_excerpt`,`post_status`,`comment_status`,`ping_status`,`post_password`,`post_name`,`to_ping`,`pinged`,`post_modified`,`post_modified_gmt`,`post_content_filtered`,`post_parent`,`guid`,`menu_order`,`post_type`,`post_mime_type`,`comment_count`) VALUES ('234','3','2013-06-05 19:58:52','2013-06-05 19:58:52','<p>We understand the benefit and positive aspects of having our employees attend conferences to increase their experience and bring fresh ideas back to the company and to their projects.Â  We want to help defray expenses when employees attend conferences that would benefit their job.Â  However, as much as we would like to support it, it is not feasible for every employee to attend every conference that might have helpful material.Â  We have therefore developed a conference attendance policy to help answer questions.</p><p>Attendance at a conference would fall into several categories, and be handled differently in each case:</p><ul><li><strong>Company-sponsored</strong>: In some cases, it is completely to the benefit of the company or a customer for an employee to attend a conference.Â  Usually, when this happens, management will approach the employee about attending the conference.Â  In this situation, all expenses for the conference, lodging, and food are reimbursed by the company, and all time is paid (no usage of paid time off required).Â  Approval from executive management prior to conference attendance would be required for an employee to be authorized to get full reimbursement and paid time for a conference.</li><li><strong>Company-supported</strong>:Â Some conferences have benefit to the company but are not critical for the current job or project position.Â Â  If an employee would like to attend a conference due to their own interest but that is work-related, they can be approved to have the company reimburse some portion of expenses, and have the time spent at the conference paid (no usage of paid time off required).Â  The company will usually agree to 50% reimbursement up to $1000 for conference/lodging/food expenses.Â  Approval from executive management prior to conference attendance would be required for an employee to be authorized to get partial reimbursement and paid time for a conference.</li><li><strong>Company-approved</strong>:Â If an employee wants to attend a conference that is only partially work-related, not related to the job the employee is currently working on, or if they have already attended a company-supported or company-sponsored conference in the last twelve months, they may still attend a conference and have their time paid so that no usage of paid time off is necessary.Â  Approval from immediate management and notification of executive management is necessary to be authorized to get paid time for a conference.</li><li><strong>Non-company-related</strong>:Â If a conference that an employee desires to attend is not related to work in any way, or if the employee has already attended a company-approved conference in the past twelve months, there will be no recompense offered from the company, and the employee must use paid or unpaid time off in order to attend.Â  Approval from immediate management is necessary to take time off from work to attend a conference.</li></ul><p><strong>After returning from a company-sponsored or company-supported conference,Â </strong>it is expected that the employee will present the learnings from that conference in some way.Â  Examples are:</p><ul><li>Present a Lunch and Learn on one or more new ideas or concepts learned at the conference.</li><li>Write up a white paper/report on some aspect of the conference and make it available to the employees.</li><li>Type up notes in readable format and publish to the corporate wiki.</li></ul><p>This will hopefully answer most questions about conference attendance.Â  Please note that this policy as written above is not granted as a right to employees and is subject to change or re-interpretation by company management at any time.Â  Paid conference attendance is a privilege and not an employee benefit, and so employees should not feel entitled to having paid conference attendance granted to them.Â  All conference attendance should be discussed and approved by immediate management in any situation.</p>','Attending Conferences','','publish','open','open','','attending-conferences','','','2013-06-05 19:58:52','2013-06-05 19:58:52','','0','https://intra-dev.asynchrony.com/help-article/attending-conferences/','0','help-article','','0');
