INSERT INTO `wp_posts` (`ID`,`post_author`,`post_date`,`post_date_gmt`,`post_content`,`post_title`,`post_excerpt`,`post_status`,`comment_status`,`ping_status`,`post_password`,`post_name`,`to_ping`,`pinged`,`post_modified`,`post_modified_gmt`,`post_content_filtered`,`post_parent`,`guid`,`menu_order`,`post_type`,`post_mime_type`,`comment_count`) VALUES ('276','3','2013-06-06 19:43:25','2013-06-06 19:43:25','<p>Asynchrony families are always expanding.Â  To assist employees with the expansion of their families, Asynchrony offers its employees choices during these times.Â </p><p>Please submit a helpdesk ticket or setup a calendar appointment to discuss your situation and options available to you.</p><p>Asynchrony employees taking more than 3 working days off for the birth or adoption of a child will need to be put on a Leave of Absence.Â  Any Asynchrony employee requesting FMLA Leave should give their immediate supervisor and HR department sufficient notice of no less than 10 business days when foreseeable.Â  Should employee need to request time off for a Leave of Absence, please contact HR to find out important information and responsibilities during a leave of absence.</p><p>Asynchrony employees are requested to add the time off to the Out of Office Calendar.Â  You, as the employee, are still responsible for reporting your hours up to the first day of Leave, in Ace, in a timely fashion.Â  Should you be unable to report your time while you are on leave, please setup an appointment with the accounting team, to discuss your situation in advance.</p><p>Should employee need to request time off for a Leave of Absence, employee\'s responsibilities during a leave of absence are:</p><p>Â </p><p>1.Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Employee must notify Asynchrony\'s HR Department of the request 30 days prior to the start of the leave, if the leave is foreseeable, or as soon as possible if the leave is not foreseeable.</p><p>2.Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Employee must notify Asynchrony\'s HR Department of any changes to the information previously submitted prior to the start of the leave, such as:</p><p>a.Â Â A change to the last day worked.</p><p>b.Â Â A change in the anticipated return date.</p><p>c.Â Â The employee no longer requires a leave of absence.</p><p>d.Â Â File disability claim, if applicable.</p><p>Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â i.Â Â Â CIGNA Disability claims can be filed by calling 800-362-4462.</p><p>1.Â Â Information needed for filling a claims:</p><p>a.Â Â name, address, and telephone number of treating providers (you and/or hospital);</p><p>b.Â Â last day worked, or date of injury or onset of illness;</p><p>c.Â Â dates of the first, last and next visit with you; supervisor\'s name, telephone number and email address;</p><p>d.Â Â <a href=\"http://www.cigna.com/sites/toolkit/physicians_disability/home/reference/terms.htm#o-p\">other income sources</a>Â (for example, Workers\' Compensation, Social Security, state disability or pension). This information may affect your patient\'s disability benefits.</p><p>Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â ii.Â Â Â The disability benefit is only payable for the amount of time that you are physically unable to work, although you might have an approved leave of absence that lasts longer. For normal childbirth with no complications, CIGNA assumes a six week period during which you would be physically unable to work. Subtract the two week waiting period and you will be paid benefits for four weeks. If the birth is by c-section the medical recovery time is assumed to be eight weeks; subtract the two week waiting period and you will paid benefits for six weeks. However, the disability benefit may be extended if there are complications or if your doctor puts you on bed rest before the baby is born.</p><p>e.Â Â Continue payment of contributions of group Health Care Flexible Spending Account, if elected during unpaid leave (payroll deductions will automatically continue if the employee continues to receive payment).</p><p>f.Â Â Continue payment of 401(k) loans, if applicable..</p><p>g.Â Â Continue payment of additional elected benefits, if applicable</p><p>h.Â Â Make election changes to benefit plans based on a qualifying event such as addition of a dependant or termination of coverage due to obtaining other coverage.Â  This must be completed within 30 days of qualifying event through the Employease system.Â  Please see below*.</p><p>i.Â Â Provide the date of birth of the new born to the Leave and Disability Group if leave is pregnancy related.</p><p>j.Â Â Provide physicianâs release upon return to work, if applicable.</p><p>k.Â Â Re-enroll in benefit plans within 30 days of eligibility following the return to work, of benefits were terminated at the end of 12 weeks of leave or for nonpayment of contributions.</p><p>l.Â Â Employee may use available Personal Time Off, starting with available sick time, to supplement wages while on Leave of Absence.</p><p>Â </p><p>More information can be found at the following links.</p><ul><li><a title=\"Employee Handbook\" href=\"https://intra-dev.asynchrony.com/help-article/employee-handbook/\">Asynchrony Employee Handbook</a></li></ul><p>Â </p><p>Making changes to your elections during your special open enrollment.Â Â Most changes are required to take place within 30 days of the event date.</p><ol><li>Once logged into ADP,Â <a href=\"https://portal.adp.com/\">https://portal.adp.com</a>, go to the Benefits tab.</li><li>Click on Life Event</li><li>Choose the option that best fits your situation.</li><li>Fill in the data requested.</li></ol><p>5.Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Proof of the Qualifying Event is required for the changes to take place.Â Â Please turn this into HR as soon as possible, but no later than 30 days after event, as to not interrupt coverage.</p><p>a.Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Birth - Certificate from Hospital</p><p>b.Â Â Â Â Â Â Marriage â License or official documentation</p><p>c.Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Divorce â Legal paperwork</p><p>Additional items of consideration when adding dependents to your insurance (All forms can be found on Intranet):</p><ul><li>Changing your CIGNA information</li></ul><p>a.Â Â Due to a qualifying event, employees are able to add, change, or cancel CIGNA insurance policies.Â  Please note that you will need to fill out all required forms and you will be subject to CIGNAâs medical insurability process.Â  Your coverage will not be effective until this process is complete.</p><ul><li>Your tax withholding</li></ul><p>a.Â Â You can change your withholding at any time.Â  No event is required.</p><ul><li>Your Health Care Account (HCA) enrollment.Â </li></ul><p>a.Â Â Due to a qualifying event you are able to enroll, change, or terminate Asynchronyâs HCA benefits.Â  This must be completed within 30 days of the qualifying event.</p><p>b.Â  HCA funds may be used for Dates of Service unto and including March 15<sup>th</sup>Â of the following year.</p><p>c.Â Â Claims must be submitted by March 31<sup>st</sup>Â of the following year.</p><p>d.Â  HCA funds are âuse it or lose it.â</p><ul><li>DCRA enrollment (for daycare or before/after school care):</li></ul><p>oÂ Â Â Â Due to a qualifying event you are able to enroll, change, or terminate Asynchronyâs DCRA benefit.Â  This must be completed within 30 days of the qualifying event.</p><p>oÂ Â Â Â Only funds available can be repaid.</p><p>oÂ Â Â Â Claims must be submitted by March 31<sup>st</sup>Â of the following year.</p><p>oÂ Â Â Â DCRA funds are âuse it or lose it.â</p><ul><li>UHC:</li></ul><p>a.Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Go through special open enrollment steps above in ADP.</p><p>b.Â Â Â Â Â Â Be sure that all of the Dependents information is listed under the Personal tab and choose Dependents.</p><ul><li>Information regarding coverage, claims, doctors, and prescriptions can be found on myuhc.com.</li><li>It typically takes 1- 2 weeks to receive your cards.Â  Temporary cards can be printed off of my.uhc.com.</li></ul><