INSERT INTO `wp_posts` (`ID`,`post_author`,`post_date`,`post_date_gmt`,`post_content`,`post_title`,`post_excerpt`,`post_status`,`comment_status`,`ping_status`,`post_password`,`post_name`,`to_ping`,`pinged`,`post_modified`,`post_modified_gmt`,`post_content_filtered`,`post_parent`,`guid`,`menu_order`,`post_type`,`post_mime_type`,`comment_count`) VALUES ('383','161','2013-06-05 15:34:44','2013-06-05 15:34:44','<p><strong>ADP Self Service iPayStatements</strong></p><p>Â Earnings statements (pay stubs) and W-2 forms are accessible 24 hours per day, 7 days a week through iPayStatements. Additionally, you can make changes to your W-4 and use calculator tools to perform \"what if\" scenarios.</p><p><strong>For Self Service registration:</strong></p><p>You will need the following for iPayStatements registration:</p><h3>How to Register on ADP iPayStatements</h3><ol><li>Go to <a href=\"https://portal.adp.com\">https://portal.adp.com</a></li><li>Click on âRegister Nowâ.</li><li>Enter the Self Service Registration Pass Code which is: Schafercor-IPAY</li><li>and click on âNextâ</li><li>Enter your Identity Information<ol><li>First Name</li><li>Last NameSocial</li><li>Security Number</li><li>Date of Birth</li></ol></li><li>Click on âNextâ</li><li>Select ADP Portal as the self-service Product.</li><li>Select Paystatement to enter additional information if your identity was verified.</li><li>From your most recent pay statement, enter the following information:<ol><li>Company Code</li><li>File Number</li><li>Check/Voucher or Advice Number</li><li>Pay Date or Advice Date</li></ol></li><li>Enter your personal contact information<ol><li>First Name</li><li>Last Name</li><li>Email Address</li><li>Phone Number</li></ol></li></ol><p>You will then be prompted to complete a registration process during which you must answer a few security questions and select a password. Your password must contain between 8 to 20 characters and at least one alpha and one numeric character. You will be assigned a system generated User ID. The security questions will be used to verify your identity if you ever forget your user ID or password.</p><p>Upon completing the registration process, you may select Log On and access the Money Tab to view your pay statements.</p><p>We hope you will enjoy this new feature. We appreciate the opportunity to provide you with this exciting new way of viewing your pay information.</p><p>Upon completing the registration process, access your pay statements at https://paystatements.adp.com or elect to have an automatic email notification sent to you when your current earnings statement is available. Included in this email is a direct link to the ADP iPayStatements website.</p><p>We hope you will enjoy this new feature. We appreciate the opportunity to provide you with this exciting new way of viewing your pay information.</p><h3>To generate a new W-4:</h3><p>Type in your changes, print the form, sign it, and forward completed form for processing, as follows:</p><p><em>Asynchrony employees forward to HR/Payroll, St. Louis, MO</em></p><h3>How do I make changes to my Payroll information?</h3><p>ADP, is also a on-line benefits tool, that is Asynchrony\'s Human Resources system of record for all employees. Employees can make changes to their payroll profile by logging into this system and inputting the needed information. This is most commonly used for changing your address. Some changes due require signature. Please consult HR/Accounting should you have any questions.</p>','Payroll / Employee Information','','inherit','open','open','','194-revision','','','2013-06-05 15:34:44','2013-06-05 15:34:44','','194','https://intra-dev.asynchrony.com/194-revision/','0','revision','','0');
