around your work area. Regularly straighten and wipe down your tables so excessive dirt and dust doesnât collect. The developer tables and office furniture are not regularly cleaned by the cleaning crew.</li>\r\n\r\n<li>If you put food in the refrigerator, make sure you clean out any leftovers every Friday afternoon so as to avoid producing refrigerator science projects. Remember: you share the refrigerator with your colleagues.</li>\r\n\r\n<li>Clean up any mess you might make with water, soap and paper products in the restrooms or the locker rooms.</li>\r\n\r\n<li>If you put dishes in the dishwasher and it appears to be full, put detergent in it and run it through a wash cycle. There are post-it notes and pens in the kitchen drawers. Itâs helpful if the person who runs the dishwasher puts a note that says âCleanâ on the dishwasher door.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\nGood office etiquette also includes how we conduct ourselves. We have a cool office, and we have customers, potential customers, and special guests who visit regularly. Please be a good ambassador of our business. Whether youâre in the elevators, parking your car, or seeing members of management or the sales group giving a tour of our space, you should be mindful of how your words and deeds reflect on the company as a whole.\r\n\r\nSince its inception, Asynchrony has placed the highest value on the comfort, security, and general happiness of our employees, and we are constantly striving to improve, to innovate, and to make Asynchrony one of THE best places to work. It all begins and ends with the quality, the character, and the commitment of our people. Please do your part.\r\n','Office Etiquette','','publish','open','open','','etiquette','','','2013-06-13 11:51:32','2013-06-13 11:51:32','','20','https://intra-dev.asynchrony.com/?page_id=504','0','page','','0');
