INSERT INTO `wp_posts` (`ID`,`post_author`,`post_date`,`post_date_gmt`,`post_content`,`post_title`,`post_excerpt`,`post_status`,`comment_status`,`ping_status`,`post_password`,`post_name`,`to_ping`,`pinged`,`post_modified`,`post_modified_gmt`,`post_content_filtered`,`post_parent`,`guid`,`menu_order`,`post_type`,`post_mime_type`,`comment_count`) VALUES ('516','161','2013-06-04 20:47:00','2013-06-04 20:47:00','<h3><a href=\"http://www.myuhcdental.com/presence/release/memberlogin.asp?action=login\">UHC Dental</a></h3><p>UHC want to make it easier for you UHC understands how important it is to have choices. Thatâs why with our Dental Options PPO plan, you can see any dentist you choose â in the network or not. You have access to our nationwide network of dentists. And when you see a dentist in our network, you save money and you wonât have to submit a claim form. Some of the advantages of using network dental providers are:</p><p>â¢ You pay lower out-of-pocket costs â¢ You have access to a broad network of dentists and specialists</p><p>â¢ We require network dentists to meet strict standards defined by the National Association of Dental Plans</p><p>â¢ You can visit any network specialist without a referral</p><p>â¢ You wonât have to file any claim forms To locate a participating network dentist:</p><p>â¢ You can view the online directory available viaÂ <a title=\"www.myuhcdental.com\" href=\"http://www.myuhcdental.com/\">www.myuhcdental.com</a></p><p>â¢ You can call Customer Care at the toll-free number listed on your dental ID card</p><p>â¢ You also can see a dentist outside of our network if you like, only at higher out-of-pocket expenses. The only time you have to submit a claim is if you visit a non-network dentist. Simply pay for the service, and then submit a completed claim form to us. We will reimburse you once youâve met your deductible.</p><p>â¢ If your current dentist is not participating in the Dental Options PPO Plan, you can nominate him/her to join the network:</p><p>o Call UnitedHealthcare Dental toll-free at 1-877-816-3596 during the hours of 8 a.m. to 11 p.m. Eastern Time, Monday through Friday o To nominate a dentist, provide your dentistâs name, dental practice name, address and telephone number to the UnitedHealthcare Dental representative, or go to myuhcdental.com and complete the Dentist Nomination form. The representative will forward this information to our network development team. A recruitment packet will be mailed to your dentist, and a network recruiter will follow up with your dentist after the packet is sent to discuss potential qualification and participation in the Dental Options PPO network.</p>','Health Care - Dental','','inherit','open','open','','190-revision','','','2013-06-04 20:47:00','2013-06-04 20:47:00','','190','https://intra-dev.asynchrony.com/190-revision/','0','revision','','0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` (`ID`,`post_author`,`post_date`,`post_date_gmt`,`post_content`,`post_title`,`post_excerpt`,`post_status`,`comment_status`,`ping_status`,`post_password`,`post_name`,`to_ping`,`pinged`,`post_modified`,`post_modified_gmt`,`post_content_filtered`,`post_parent`,`guid`,`menu_order`,`post_type`,`post_mime_type`,`comment_count`) VALUES ('517','170','2013-05-31 22:19:30','2013-05-31 22:19:30','<p>Organizing a meetingÂ is not difficult, but you will need to download and log in to the GoToMeeting software with a valid account.Â  Asynchrony owns four licenses to GoToMeeting, and licenses cannot be used simultaneously.Â </p><p>Any team is welcome to use either of these accounts, but each account can only be used for one meeting at a time. Â <b>PLEASE make sure the account is not in use</b>Â before you schedule a meetingÂ by adding the appropriate \"GoToMeeting-\" resourceÂ when you set up your appointmentÂ in Zimbra.</p><h2>Overview</h2><p>Meetings can be as long as you desire, with up to 25 participants.Â  We pay a flat monthly fee for the service, so it does not matter how many meetings we hold however they can only be used 1 meeting at a time.</p><div><p><strong>Â Here are the licenses you can use:</strong></p></div><ul><li><a href=\"mailto:gtm-blue@asynchrony.com\">gtm-blue@asynchrony.com</a></li><li><a href=\"mailto:gtm-orange@asynchrony.com\">gtm-orange@asynchrony.com</a></li><li><a href=\"mailto:gtm-black@asynchrony.com\">gtm-black@asynchrony.com</a></li><li><a href=\"mailto:sales-team@asynchrony.com\">sales-team@asynchrony.com</a>Â should be used byÂ the Asynchrony sales team.</li></ul><p><strong>The password for all of these accounts is:</strong>Â <em>4asynchrony</em></p><h2>Setup</h2><p>If you are organizing the meeting for a project, you probably have one of these licenses assigned for your project to use.Â  If not, you may use one of these licenses,Â <strong>provided you verify that it is available</strong>. Each license has a Zimbra resource account assigned to it. Â You can check on the availability of the GoToMeeting account and reserve it, just like you can conference rooms, through the \"Resources\" option in Zimbra appointments. Â Just click the \"Show Equipment\" link to the right of the Location field as shown below,<b>and start typing \"GoToMeeting\";</b>Â the choices should appear and availability will be shown on the calendar below the appointment information.</p><ol><li>GoToMeeting works on Windows and Macintosh operating systems, so make sure you are using a computer with one of those operating systems booted up, and that is connected to the Internet.</li><li>Navigate toÂ <a href=\"http://www.gotomeeting.com/\" target=\"_blank\">www.gotomeeting.com</a>Â and click the button that says \"Host a Meeting\".</li><li>The software will automatically be downloaded to your computer, and you will need to enter the username and password for the account you plan to use.</li><li>If you want to create an ad hoc meeting right now, choose \"Meet Now\"Â when prompted.</li><li>If you want to schedule a meeting for a future time (or set a recurring meeting), choose \"Schedule Meeting\"Â when prompted.</li></ol><h2>Some Notes To Remember</h2><ul><li>We do not normally use GoToMeeting audio services, we use our own conference lines.Â  During the meeting (or in the scheduling dialog) you can choose \"Provide your own conference call information\"Â and type in the instructions for accessing our conference line.</li><li>Once the meeting has started, other participants can join.Â  They will need the meeting number and the password, if you provided one.</li><li>When participants join, they will not see your screen until you press the \"Show My Screen\"Â button (which looks like an audio play button).</li><li>You can freeze the display at any time (for example, if you need to access email or go to another site and don\'t want to be distracting)Â by pressing the \"Show My Screen\"Â button when it looks like an audio pause button.</li><li>You can give keyboard and mouse control to another user, or to everyone.</li><li>You can make another user a presenter, which will change the meeting to show their desktop instead of yours.</li><li>If you set up a recurring meeting in the account, please note that this meeting is ONLY available with the account where it was set up (i.e. you can\'t set it up with one account and host the meeting with the other).</li></ul><p>Â </p>','Organizing a GoToMeeting','','inherit','open','open','','165-revision-2','','','2013-05-31 22:19:30','2013-05-31 22:19:30','','165','https://intra-dev.asynchrony.com/165-revision-2/','0','revision','','0');
