INSERT INTO `wp_posts` (`ID`,`post_author`,`post_date`,`post_date_gmt`,`post_content`,`post_title`,`post_excerpt`,`post_status`,`comment_status`,`ping_status`,`post_password`,`post_name`,`to_ping`,`pinged`,`post_modified`,`post_modified_gmt`,`post_content_filtered`,`post_parent`,`guid`,`menu_order`,`post_type`,`post_mime_type`,`comment_count`) VALUES ('541','161','2013-06-05 19:57:05','2013-06-05 19:57:05','<p>At Asynchrony Solutions, we know that the most valuable asset any company can have is their people. That is why we take pride in having some of the best employees in the industry. Our people enjoy a structured, yet relaxed, work environment with excellent benefits and opportunities.</p><h4>Referral Bonus</h4><hr /><p>To encourage your proactive assistance in helping Asynchrony Solutions find the right people to add to our team, we will pay up to a $2,500 bonus to employees who refer a new employee that we hire and who stays with Asynchrony for at least 90 days (the bonus to be paid after the 90 day time period).</p><p>We are currently hiring Mid-Sr level canidates for the following positions:</p><ul><li>Sr. Java Developers and/or Architects</li><li>iPad/iPhone Developers</li><li>Mid Level Java Candidates</li><li>Java Developers with Android Experience</li><li>Java/.NET combination candidates</li><li>Enterprise Architects</li><li>.Net Software Engineers</li></ul><p>For referrals to be eligible for the bonus program, the should apply online atÂ <a href=\"http://www.asolutions.com/aboutus-careers.html\" target=\"_blank\">jobs.asolutions.com</a>Â indicating they are a referral from you.Â  You should also send aÂ  brief write-up describing the person\'s skills and expertise to Sandi.Â </p><p>Your referral email should include:</p><ul><li>How you know the canidate</li><li>How the candidate will best fit within our organization</li><li>Anything else we should know about the referral</li></ul><h5><em>Asynchrony is an Equal Employment Opportunity Employer</em></h5><p>Â </p><p>Note:Â  Recruiters are not eligible to receive referral bonuses.Â  Supervisors and other levels of management involved in the hiring decision process are not eligible to receive referral bonuses for applicants they refer if the applicant is hired for a position reporting directly or indirectly to them.Â Â If a referred applicant is hired through an agency, a referral bonus will not be paid. Not all positions qualify for a referral bonus.<b><strong></strong></b></p><p>Â </p>','Recruiting & Referral Bonus','','inherit','open','open','','232-revision','','','2013-06-05 19:57:05','2013-06-05 19:57:05','','232','https://intra-dev.asynchrony.com/232-revision/','0','revision','','0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` (`ID`,`post_author`,`post_date`,`post_date_gmt`,`post_content`,`post_title`,`post_excerpt`,`post_status`,`comment_status`,`ping_status`,`post_password`,`post_name`,`to_ping`,`pinged`,`post_modified`,`post_modified_gmt`,`post_content_filtered`,`post_parent`,`guid`,`menu_order`,`post_type`,`post_mime_type`,`comment_count`) VALUES ('542','161','2013-06-12 19:49:53','2013-06-12 19:49:53','<p>After hours and on weekends, Asynchronyâs downtown and IL offices are protected with an alarm system. Every employee will be assigned an alarm code that can be used to turn the alarm on and off. There are multiple alarm pad locations you should familiarize yourself with in case you are the first to arrive or the last to leave, or if you are working over the weekend.Â </p><p>For security purposes, Cupples 9 management also programs the elevators to a secure mode after hours and on weekends, so you will need to use your key card to gain access to both of Asynchronyâs floors during these times.Â </p><h3>Cupples 9 Alarm Pad Locations:</h3><ul><li>6<sup>th</sup> Floor Secure Space (south side) â one inside each entrance</li><li>6<sup>th</sup> Floor Open Space (north side) â inside the entrance door to the right as you exit the elevator</li><li>Forest Park Conference Room â on either side of the room inside both entrances</li><li>7<sup>th</sup> Floor â by the stairwell door in the reception/lobby area</li></ul><h3>Seibert Rd Alarm Pad Locations:</h3><ul><li>Main entrance</li><li>Side entrance by the coffee maker</li><li>Back of office by the kitchen</li></ul><p>Â </p><h3>The Alarm is going off.</h3><p>If you enter a work area and hear the alarm pad beeping, it means you were the first to enter the space since the alarm was set the following evening. You must enter your code and press the OFF button to keep the alarm from activating and notifying the authorities. If you are the last person to leave a work area, it is your responsibility to set the alarm. Enter your code and press the AWAY button. The alarm pad will start beeping, and you have 90 seconds to exit the area without setting off the alarm.</p><h3>Oops, I set off the alarm.</h3><p>Should you accidentally set off the alarm, please immediately call the Alarm Hotline: 314.735.7698.</p><p>Â </p>','Security & Alarm Systems','','inherit','open','open','','206-revision-3','','','2013-06-12 19:49:53','2013-06-12 19:49:53','','206','https://intra-dev.asynchrony.com/206-revision-3/','0','revision','','0');
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` (`ID`,`post_author`,`post_date`,`post_date_gmt`,`post_content`,`post_title`,`post_excerpt`,`post_status`,`comment_status`,`ping_status`,`post_password`,`post_name`,`to_ping`,`pinged`,`post_modified`,`post_modified_gmt`,`post_content_filtered`,`post_parent`,`guid`,`menu_order`,`post_type`,`post_mime_type`,`comment_count`) VALUES ('545','201','2013-06-07 18:15:30','2013-06-07 18:15:30','<p>If you\'re not at the office but need to get work done, you can always use our safe and secure Virtual Private Network.Â A VPN is a private network that uses a public network to connect remote sites or users together. The VPN uses \"virtual\" connections routedÂ through the Internet from the business\'s private network to the remote site or employee. By using a VPN, businesses ensure security -- anyone intercepting the encrypted dataÂ can\'t read it.</p><p>You can download the Citrix AnyConnectÂ client from <a href=\"http://vpn.asolutions.com\">http://vpn.asolutions.com</a></p><p>Â </p><h4><strong>Windows and Mac</strong></h4><p><strong></strong>Once you have downloaded and launched the AnyConnect client</p><ul><li>Connect to:Â <strong>vpn.asolutions.com</strong></li><li>Choose Asynchrony form the Group and enter your Username and Password</li></ul><p>Â </p><h4><strong>Linux</strong></h4><p>Install the following packages to use the VPN:</p><ul><li>apt-get install network-manager-openconnect</li><li>Reboot</li><li>Once installed, left-click on the Network Manager icon and choose \"VPNÂ Connections\" -&gt; \"Configure VPN\"</li><li>Click <strong>\"Add\"</strong> and setup your connection with UsernameÂ </li><li>From network manager choose VPN Connections --&gt; Asynchrony</li></ul><p>Â </p><h4>Mobile Anyconnect for iOS and Android</h4><p>Download the Cisco AnyConnect Mobile Client from the Google Play or AppStore and follow the same instructions found under Windows and Mac</p><ul><li>The first time you launch the AnyConnect client you will need to enter the following:</li><li>Connect to:Â <strong>vpn.asolutions.com</strong></li><li>Choose Asynchrony form the Group and enter your usename and password</li></ul><p>Â </p>','Working Remotely With VPN','','inherit','open','open','','167-revision-5','','','2013-06-07 18:15:30','2013-06-07 18:15:30','','167','https://intra-dev.asynchrony.com/167-revision-5/','0','revision','','0');
